[1.31174, "o", "--- Step 1: Ingest Project Chimera Q1 Report ---\r\n\r\n"]
[31.334765, "o", "Agent: {\"document_id\":\"f48791ab-b507-4b31-9799-9388378148f2\",\"content_hash\":\"5832118529bfb52193a9454d5d56c1d0c85ceac9f07103cf1348689d4ec7450f\"}\r\n"]
[31.334852, "o", "\r\n--- Step 2: Ingest Independent Risk & Safety Audit ---\r\n\r\n"]
[59.196597, "o", "Agent: {\"document_id\":\"536e76a8-3bb2-44da-b9a4-ea5164d7518e\",\"content_hash\":\"02fed40ef02a3b994af9fef05ba339d14f687716a674330e11300955fef6a7cb\"}\r\n\r\n--- Step 3: Cross-Document Synthesis (token_budget=4000) ---\r\n\r\n"]
[59.196703, "o", "Query: Compare the Q1 latency claims with the audit findings.\r\n       Are there contradictions? What do they mean for the Q4 target?\r\n\r\n"]
[65.632276, "o", "Agent: Yes—there is **no internal numerical contradiction** between the two documents, but there is a **measurement-context contradiction** (i.e., comparing latencies measured under different conditions without reconciling them).\r\n\r\n### 1) What matches (no contradiction)\r\n- **Q1 2026 report (Project Chimera):** latency is reported as **12 ms** measured **under isoflurane anaesthesia** using a **stereotaxic frame**, and explicitly **not** measured in awake/freely moving subjects.\r\n- **Q2 2026 independent audit (EAG):** states that they replicated the anaesthesia protocol and **confirmed the 12 ms figure under anaesthesia**.\r\n\r\nSo the *anaesthetized* latency claim is consistent across both.\r\n\r\n### 2) What conflicts / creates contradiction (conditions not harmonized)\r\n- **EAG adds an awake-subject measurement:** **31 ms** (awake, freely moving).\r\n- The Q1 report:\r\n  - does **not** present the awake-subject latency,\r\n  - and does **not** flag that the 12 ms figure is **anaesthesia-dependent** in the executive framing.\r\n\r\nThus, the “contradiction” is not that 12 ms is wrong—it’s that the *project’s headline target* (sub-5 ms by Q4 2026) is potentially being interpreted without fully accounting for the **awake baseline** that EAG measured.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Implications for the Q4 target\r\n- **EAG concludes sub-5 ms is “highly aggressive”** given the **awake baseline of 31 ms** and claims it would likely require both:\r\n  1) the Phase 3 ASIC, **and**\r\n  2) a **motion-compensation algorithm** not yet developed.\r\n- Therefore, the implication is that the Q4 target of **under 5 ms** (as stated) is likely **not feasible under awake-subject conditions** on the current plan/timeline, unless additional work beyond Phase 3 hardware is delivered.\r\n- EAG’s recommendation: **revise the Q4 latency target to ~15 ms** and **publish a corrected latency baseline including awake-subject conditions**.\r\n\r\nIn short: **anaesthesia latency (12 ms) is corroborated**, but **awake-subject performance (31 ms) undermines the credibility of a sub-5 ms Q4 objective unless compensatory methods are added**.\r\n"]
[65.632701, "o", "\r\n--- Step 4: Surgical Drill-Down (token_budget=150) ---\r\n\r\nQuery: What were the exact measurement conditions for the 12 ms figure?\r\n\r\n"]
[72.312296, "o", "Agent: The Q1 report states that **all latency figures (including the 12 ms value)** were obtained under the following conditions:\r\n\r\n- **Anaesthesia:** **isoflurane anaesthesia (1.5–2.0% v/v)**\r\n- **Apparatus/immobilization:** **using a stereotaxic frame**\r\n- **Subject state:** **NOT taken from freely-moving or awake subjects** (explicitly done to **eliminate motion artefacts** during the current calibration phase)\r\n\r\n--- Step 5: Same Question, Higher Budget (token_budget=2000) ---\r\n"]
[72.312531, "o", "\r\nQuery: Same question — but now with enough budget to see why it matters.\r\n\r\n"]
[76.989627, "o", "Agent: ### Exact measurement conditions for the **12 ms** latency figure (Q1 report)\r\nIn *Project Chimera: Q1 2026 Research Report*, the measurement methodology states that **all latency figures (including the 12 ms value)** were obtained:\r\n\r\n- **Anaesthesia:** “**isoflurane anaesthesia (1.5–2.0% v/v)**”\r\n- **Frame/immobilization:** “**using a stereotaxic frame**”\r\n- **Subject state / exclusions:** “**Measurements were NOT taken from freely-moving or awake subjects**”\r\n- **Stated reason/context:** “**This constraint was necessary to eliminate motion artefacts during the current calibration phase.**”\r\n\r\n### Broader context surrounding that methodology\r\nThe report frames this approach as a **calibration-phase measurement constraint**: latency results are intentionally taken **only under anaesthesia with stereotaxic immobilization** to reduce confounds from **motion artefacts**, and it explicitly notes that results are **not** representative of **freely-moving/awake** conditions (which are deferred to later “awake-subject calibration protocols” in the Q4 target section).\r\n\r\n--- Step 6: Out-of-Corpus Question (token_budget=2000) ---\r\n"]
[76.990029, "o", "\r\nQuery: Something plausible but not in either document.\r\n\r\n"]
[80.504657, "o", "Agent: In the **Q1 2026 Project Chimera Research Report**, the only animal species mentioned is **murine (mice)**—e.g., “murine trials,” “murine subjects,” and “murine.”\r\n\r\nNo other animal species (beyond mice/murine) are named, and therefore **no non-mouse species results are reported** in the Q1 report.\r\n"]
[80.504814, "o", "\r\n"]
